Public Note with Ob: Very few snowmachine tracks this time. Drilled one hole closer to south shore and drilled into the mud. Moved closer to center of lake for holes that had water at the bottom.
3" of water on top of the ice here (under the snow). We used our new\
Interal Notes: heavy-duty drill bit from Kovacs and had a much easier time trilling though our tricky lake ice. I'm curious to see how this new bit works next winter for us. We also got a nice new tape measuring system from them after the last setup broke at the beginning of the month.

column11: Observer reports\
column12: "Ice thickness at Calico bluff currently 51 inches. Mid- river main channel in area with no jumble ice. Little snowfall and high winds are keeping snow cover at a minimum all winter. River level is low. Bad freeze up at Eagle and 6 miles down stream. Extreme jumble in place. ice pack with little to no water beneath it to the bottom in many areas. I anticipate a late break up and high potential for ice jamming/flooding possible in the Eagle & Calico bluff area (14 miles downstream). Past two days are first spring thawing days. With below freeze temps at night. Bottom line as of now still winter like\
column14: no deterioration of snow pack measurable. No appreciable  loss of snow on the river yet."

column11: Stream seemed to have frozen up and Ice collapsed onto the creek bed. On both sides of the culvert the ice had collapsed onto the stream bed. We found a slight bit of water in hole #1 and just mud in the remaining holes. We used the snow depth gauge to measure depth of holes #2 and #3.
